  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section B — Baxter (TQ) solver: minimal reusable routine set (BaxterMatrix, TauEigensystem/Psi/τ, QSolve, Q1) ported from Experiments/Baxter_Solver_L2.wb. Only the load-bearing definitions are kept here; see that file for the full derivation, the spurious-vs-genuine motivation writeup (why a naive Baxter-matrix diagonalization overcounts states relative to the true weight-M subspace dimension dPred), and the validation/regression suite (stage-1 t2-eigenvalue checks and stage-2 end-to-end TQ-residual checks) that verified this pipeline. t2Coeffs below calls Section A's t2 directly (dedup: the shared companion-twist machinery lives only in Section A now).*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*a(u), d(u)=Qθ(u), and τ0 = τ minus the J term (using ee1=λ1+λ2-M, ee2=M).\n  Qθ (=d) is defined LOCALLY here so this file is self-contained.\n  qpoly builds a polynomial from an ASCENDING coefficient list {c0,...,cM} (cM=1 for monic q_n);\n  formed in a dummy symbol first so substituting uu=0 gives the constant term rather than an\n  indeterminate 0^0.*)\nClearAll[aFun, τ0, Qθ, qpoly];\naFun[λ1_, λ2_][u_] := (u - θ1 - h λ1) (u - θ2 - h λ2);\nQθ[u_] := (u - θ1) (u - θ2);\nτ0[λ1_, λ2_, M_][u_] := (κ1 + κ2) u^2 - (θ1 + θ2) (κ1 + κ2) u - u h (κ1 (λ1 + λ2 - M) + κ2 M);\nqpoly[clist_, uu_] := Module[{x}, (clist . x^Range[0, Length[clist] - 1]) /. x -> uu];\n{aFun[1, 1][u], Qθ[u], τ0[1, 1, 1][u]}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"352966\" data-output-id=\"30\" data-out-n=\"217\" data-sub-idx=\"6\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"27\" data-sub-start=\"10\" data-sub-end=\"10\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[217]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrnhejnf-8luta15\" data-page-width-em=\"21\" data-latex-b64=\"\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.4em;vertical-align:-0.95em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">{</span></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">(</span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">u</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.3214em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.314em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.677em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">4</span></span></span></span>