  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section E — operatorial factorization of the L=2 SoV basis. Builds a genuine STANDALONE\n  length-1 (single-site) fused transfer-matrix hierarchy t1[λ][a,s] and SoV covector xL1[λ][{s}]\n  (the paper's L=1 construction), then verifies that the s2=0 slice of the L=2 SoV basis factorizes\n  as x2[λ1,λ2][{s1,0}] = c (xL1[λ1][{s1}] ⊗ xSingle[λ2][{0}]) up to a scalar c fixed by the\n  Qθ-vs-Qθ1 normalization mismatch. Sections A–D are read-only.\n  See docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-16-xxx-sov-factorization-functional-overlap-design.md.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Single-site (L=1) fused transfer matrices — the L=1 analogue of Section A's two-site t2 block,\n  built from the SAME single-site Lax L[λ] (no θ baked in) and shared companion twist G. qdet1 is\n  the single-site quantum determinant: both factors are this site's L evaluated at u-θ1 and u-θ1-h\n  (the internal -h shift), unlike the two-site qdetT where θ is already in T. t1[λ][1,1](u)=tr_a[G\n  L(u-θ1)] matches paper eq. t_{1,1}(u)=tr_a[G L(u-θ)].*)\nClearAll[t1, qdet1];\nt1[λ_][0, s_][u_] := IdentityMatrix[dim[{λ, 0}]];\nt1[λ_][a_, 0][u_] := IdentityMatrix[dim[{λ, 0}]];\nt1[λ_][1, 1][u_] := Sum[L[λ][i, j][u - θ1] G[[j, i]], {i, 2}, {j, 2}];\nqdet1[λ_][u_] := L[λ][1, 1][u - θ1] . L[λ][2, 2][u - θ1 - h] - L[λ][2, 1][u - θ1] . L[λ][1, 2][u - θ1 - h];\nt1[λ_][2, 1][u_] := χ2 qdet1[λ][u];\nt1[λ_][1, s_ /; s > 1][u_] := t1[λ][1, s - 1][u] . t1[λ][1, 1][u + (s - 1) h] - t1[λ][2, 1][u + (s - 1) h] . t1[λ][1, s - 2][u];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*smoke: shape check for the fused hierarchy*)\n{Dimensions[t1[2][1,1][u]], Dimensions[t1[2][1,2][u]]}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"352966\" data-output-id=\"47\" data-out-n=\"316\" data-sub-idx=\"1\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"54\" data-sub-start=\"1\" data-sub-end=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[316]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrnhflyt-s22gudo\" data-page-width-em=\"21\" data-latex-b64=\"XGJlZ2lue3BtYXRyaXh9MyAmIDNcXDMgJiAzXGVuZHtwbWF0cml4fQ==\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.4em;vertical-align:-0.95em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">(</span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mtable\"><span class=\"col-align-c\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.45em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.61em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-2.41em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.95em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"arraycolsep\" style=\"width:0.5em;\"></span><span class=\"arraycolsep\" style=\"width:0.5em;\"></span><span class=\"col-align-c\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.45em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.61em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-2.41em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.95em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[316]= \\begin{pmatrix}3 & 3\\\\3 & 3\\end{pmatrix}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "7782eef0-e1eb-421d-9841-7dbcd30e84f5"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Genuine length-1 SoV covector (paper normalization, 1-site Qθ1(u)=u-θ1). xSingle[λ][{0}] is the\n  site lowest-weight covector (Section A) — a 1×(λ+1) row. xL1 stays that shape: (1×n).(n×n)=1×n.\n  B1 is the L=1 SoV B-operator.*)\nClearAll[B1, xL1];\nB1[λ_][u_] := L[λ][1, 1][u - θ1];\nxL1[λ_][{0}] := xSingle[λ][{0}];\nxL1[λ_][{s_}] := xL1[λ][{s}] = xSingle[λ][{0}] . t1[λ][1, s][θ1] / Product[Qθ1[θ1 - λ h + (p - 1) h], {p, 1, s}];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Internal check (independent of the factorization): xL1[λ][{s}] must be a LEFT eigencovector of\n  B1 with eigenvalue u-θ1-s h — the paper's L=1 SoV property (verified there symbolically for\n  λ=1..5). This validates the whole t1/xL1 construction before it is used downstream. Symbolic in\n  u; residual Chopped at the 10^-20 noise floor.*)\nxL1BCheck = Table[\n   xL1[λ][{s}] . B1[λ][u] - (u - θ1 - s h) xL1[λ][{s}],\n   {λ, 1, 3}, {s, 0, λ}] // ExpandAll // Chop[#, 10^-20] & // Flatten // Union;\nxL1BCheck",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"352966\" data-output-id=\"48\" data-out-n=\"322\" data-sub-idx=\"2\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"56\" data-sub-start=\"7\" data-sub-end=\"7\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[322]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrnhfmfk-x7v7v3q\" data-page-width-em=\"21\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRcezBccmlnaHRcfQ==\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[322]= \\left\\{0\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "71c6496d-463b-44d9-a85d-8745bfe43f89"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Operatorial factorization: x2[λ1,λ2][{s1,0}] = c (xL1[λ1][{s1}] ⊗ xSingle[λ2][{0}]). Flatten both\n  to length-D vectors, take the component ratio over the nonzero components of the tensor product.\n  HARD requirement #1: the ratio lhs/tp must be a CONSTANT c (spread below the 10^-15 floor) — the\n  actual factorization content (\"t2[1,s1][θ1] acts only through a rank-1 site-2 eigenvalue\"). HARD\n  requirement #2 (hardened after the μEff≠1 finding was pinned down): c must equal the CORRECTED\n  scalar cPredCorr[λ1,λ2,s1] = Product[(θ1-θ2+(k-1)h-λ2 h)/(θ1-θ2+(k-1)h-λ1 h),{k,1,s1}], which\n  accounts for the genuine site-2 passthrough eigenvalue μSite2[λ2,s1] (defined/verified at the\n  operator level in the cell below) — NOT the naive 1/Product[(θ1-λ1 h+(k-1)h)-θ2,{k,1,s1}] that\n  assumed a trivial (identity) site-2 passthrough. cPredCorr reduces to 1 at λ1=λ2 and to\n  f(λ2)/f(λ1), f(λ)=21λ-4, at s1=1 — matching the earlier empirical finding exactly. mueff=cval/cpred\n  is now a closure check (must be exactly 1 to the noise floor) rather than a soft warning.*)\nClearAll[cPredCorr];\ncPredCorr[λ1_, λ2_, s1_] := Product[(θ1 - θ2 + (k - 1) h - λ2 h)/(θ1 - θ2 + (k - 1) h - λ1 h), {k, 1, s1}];\nSoVFact::notconst = \"Ratio lhs/tp not constant for (λ1,λ2,s1)=(`1`,`2`,`3`): spread=`4`.\";\nSoVFact::mu = \"c ≠ cPredCorr for (λ1,λ2,s1)=(`1`,`2`,`3`): μEff=`4` (corrected scalar formula failed — a construction bug, not a finding).\";\nfactResults = Flatten[Table[\n    Module[{lhs, tp, nz, rl, cval, cpred, mueff, spread},\n     lhs = Flatten[x2[λ1, λ2][{s1, 0}]];\n     tp = Flatten[KroneckerProduct[xL1[λ1][{s1}], xSingle[λ2][{0}]]];\n     nz = Position[tp, x_ /; Abs[Chop[x, 10^-20]] > 10^-12];\n     rl = Extract[lhs, nz]/Extract[tp, nz];\n     cval = Mean[rl];\n     spread = Max[Abs[rl - cval]];\n     cpred = cPredCorr[λ1, λ2, s1];\n     mueff = cval/cpred;\n     If[spread > 10^-15, Message[SoVFact::notconst, λ1, λ2, s1, N[spread]]; Abort[]];\n     If[Abs[N[mueff - 1]] > 10^-15, Message[SoVFact::mu, λ1, λ2, s1, N[mueff]]; Abort[]];  (* now HARD *)\n     {λ1, λ2, s1, cval, cpred, N[mueff], N[spread]}],\n    {λ1, 1, 3}, {λ2, 1, 3}, {s1, 0, λ1}], 2];\nColumn[factResults]",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
